Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.56,0:00:40.56,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1\i0}关注左岸电影微信公众号：film-zone
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.56,0:01:13.73,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"Boundaries of...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.19,0:01:17.56,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"propriety...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.23,0:01:25.99,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"vigorously assaulted...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.75,0:01:37.75,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"... propriety were... "
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.64,0:02:36.89,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"The boundaries of propriety were vigorously assaulted.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.31,0:02:40.94,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"The boundaries of propriety were vigorously assaulted as was only right
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.02,0:02:43.61,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"but not quite breached as was also right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.69,0:02:45.19,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"Nevertheless
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.61,0:02:49.24,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"she was not pleased."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.51,0:03:12.05,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- What is it? - Jane.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.26,0:03:14.35,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.90,0:03:27.40,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Jane!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.98,0:03:32.61,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.24,0:03:35.45,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh dear me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.58,0:03:38.79,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,That girl needs a husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.20,0:03:42.67,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,And who's good enough? Nobody.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.00,0:03:46.34,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I blame you for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.42,0:03:49.01,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Being too much the model of perfection.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.17,0:03:53.26,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I've shared your bed for 32 years
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.34,0:03:57.56,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,and perfection is something I have not encountered.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.64,0:03:58.72,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.23,0:04:07.15,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,No. Stop it. Mr Austen it's Sunday! Stop no it's...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.49,0:04:16.70,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,The utmost of a woman's character is expressed in the duties of daughter
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.99,0:04:22.96,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,sister and eventually wife and mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.96,0:04:26.19,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,It is secured by soft attraction virtuous
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.91,0:04:31.10,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,love and quiet in the early morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.88,0:04:36.09,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,If a woman happens to have a particular superiority
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.18,0:04:40.93,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,for example a profound mind it is best kept a profound secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.10,0:04:45.27,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Humour is liked more but wit? No.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.31,0:04:49.36,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,It is the most treacherous talent of them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.44,0:04:53.61,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Now George old fellow you know you have to stay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.70,0:04:55.41,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Jenny! - George George.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.50,0:05:05.75,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry along Jane! We'll be late!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.62,0:05:09.71,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,When Her Ladyship calls we must obey.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.58,0:05:42.74,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Come along Jane.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.38,0:05:57.47,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Lady Gresham may I introduce my niece Comtesse De Feuillide
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.39,0:06:02.35,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,and Mr Fowle Cassandra's fiance.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.43,0:06:08.06,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Comtesse? Then you presume to be French? - By marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.14,0:06:11.02,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Monsieur le Comte is not here to pay his respects?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.11,0:06:13.23,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,A prior engagement ma'am
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.32,0:06:17.03,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Monsieur le Comte was obliged to pay his respects to Madame le Guillotine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.11,0:06:18.20,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.57,0:06:24.79,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I see your nephew is with us again.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.87,0:06:26.25,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr Wisley.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.33,0:06:30.21,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Wisley is indispensable to my happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.80,0:06:36.71,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Well do sit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.10,0:06:47.06,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr Fowle and Cassandra are only recently engaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.31,0:06:50.10,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,When shall you marry?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.19,0:06:52.61,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Not for some time Your Ladyship. - Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.69,0:06:54.82,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm also engaged to go to the West Indies
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.90,0:06:58.24,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,with Lord Craven's expedition against the French as chaplain.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.32,0:07:03.58,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- What has Craven offered you? - I've hopes of a parish on my return.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.66,0:07:05.54,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,How much is it worth?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.29,0:07:09.87,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Enough to marry on in a modest way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.71,0:07:20.18,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr Wisley did you know the Basingstoke assemblies resume?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.26,0:07:23.14,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Very soon I believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.22,0:07:27.68,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Jane does enjoy a ball. - Wisley can't abide them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.23,0:07:34.56,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,But sir
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.15,0:07:39.78,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,a ball is an indispensable blessing to the juvenile part of the neighbourhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.86,0:07:43.07,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything agreeable in the way of talking and sitting down together
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.16,0:07:45.78,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,all managed with the utmost decorum.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.62,0:07:49.04,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,An amiable man could not object.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.29,0:07:56.42,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I find I'm converted.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.17,0:08:00.17,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Displayed like a brood mare.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.26,0:08:04.93,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Mr Wisley is a highly eligible young gentleman. - Oh Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.01,0:08:08.60,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- You know our situation Jane. - Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.68,0:08:12.44,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,And he is Lady Gresham's favourite nephew and heir.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.52,0:08:15.19,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,One day he shall inherit this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.56,0:08:18.90,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Excellent prospects!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.53,0:08:30.25,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- His small fortune will not buy me. - What will buy you cousin?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.96,0:08:39.75,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,More wary in the world Mr Lefroy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.10,0:08:48.97,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,You can pay me for that later.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.06,0:08:51.81,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Huzzah! Huzzah! - Come on Mr Lefroy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.65,0:09:01.40,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on man hit him!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.40,0:09:03.65,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Lefroy!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.83,0:09:20.30,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Glass of wine with you sir? - Madam.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.68,0:09:31.68,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Displaying to advantage I see Lefroy. - Like the sword Austen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.98,0:09:35.85,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,How long before you have to get back to the sticks?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.94,0:09:37.52,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,A day.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.60,0:09:38.90,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,So soon?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.98,0:09:42.65,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Doghouse debts but one must cut some sort of a figure even in the militia.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.73,0:09:45.78,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Especially when condemned to a parsonage my friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.86,0:09:46.99,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.07,0:09:52.37,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Still who is this sour - faced little virgin?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.45,0:09:54.29,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Your pardon ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.96,0:09:59.46,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr Tom Lefroy may I present Mr John Warren?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.54,0:10:04.01,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Joining me in Hampshire my father is preparing us both for holy orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.09,0:10:07.76,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand you've visited Hampshire Mr Lefroy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.84,0:10:09.34,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.72,0:10:13.93,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Long visit was it? - Very long Mr Warren. Almost three hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.22,0:10:17.69,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr Austen you're devilishly handsome. A kiss a kiss.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.77,0:10:19.40,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Oops!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.06,0:10:23.15,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,So Tom where should we go? Vauxhall Gardens?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.23,0:10:24.73,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Been there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.82,0:10:27.49,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Lefroy there's a Tahitian Love Fest on at White's.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.57,0:10:28.66,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Seen it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.74,0:10:30.91,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Crockford's? - Crockford's? Done that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.99,0:10:32.83,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Or did it do me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.91,0:10:36.16,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh - wh - wh - what is a Tahitian Love Fest?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.88,0:10:48.47,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Warren!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.60,0:11:02.94,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I humbly beg your pardon sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.82,0:11:09.40,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Theft of one pig is a crime heinous to be sure but two pigs...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.16,0:11:15.51,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Two pigs is a violent assault on the very
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.52,0:11:18.84,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,sanctity of private property itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.33,0:11:23.42,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.50,0:11:29.09,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,You and your kind are a canker on the body social.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.43,0:11:34.68,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,And cankers are cut out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.68,0:11:38.73,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Transportation for life. Next.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.98,0:11:43.98,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Why are you here in London sir? - To learn the law.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.06,0:11:48.44,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Which has no other end but what? - The preservation of the rights of property.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.53,0:11:51.24,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Against? - The mob.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.32,0:11:56.74,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore order is kept because we have...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.83,0:12:00.79,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- A standing army? - Good manners sir and prudence.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.87,0:12:03.71,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Do you know that word? Prudence? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.67,0:12:07.67,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Consider myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.80,0:12:13.51,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I was born rich certainly but I remain rich by virtue of exceptional conduct.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.68,0:12:16.05,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I have shown restraint.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.56,0:12:21.10,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Your mother my sister became poor because she did not...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.18,0:12:22.73,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,She married my father because she loved him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.81,0:12:26.86,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes and that's why you have so many brothers and sisters back there in...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.94,0:12:28.53,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Limerick. - Mmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.53,0:12:34.66,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,If you hope I say hope...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.74,0:12:39.41,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,If you aspire to inherit my property
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.79,0:12:44.79,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,you must prove yourself more worthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.87,0:12:47.79,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,But what do we find? We find dissipation
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.88,0:12:52.42,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,wild enough to glut the imaginings of a Hottentot braggadocio.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.59,0:12:57.18,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Wild companions gambling
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.39,0:13:02.10,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,running around St James's like a neck - or - nothing young blood of the fancy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.18,0:13:05.35,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- What kind of lawyer will that make? - Typical.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.07,0:13:14.70,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Humour?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.07,0:13:20.37,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Well you're going to need that because I'm teaching you a lesson.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.58,0:13:28.17,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sending you to stay with your other relations the Lefroys.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.30,0:13:36.01,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Uncle they live in the country. - Deep in the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.78,0:13:56.70,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Jane? - Mmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.20,0:13:58.66,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.08,0:14:02.45,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.66,0:14:06.79,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I think you two quite the prettiest sisters in England.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.21,0:14:11.38,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr Fowle will be enchanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.75,0:14:15.30,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,San Domingo is half a world away.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.97,0:14:18.84,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,He'll forget me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.93,0:14:22.43,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible. Look at the memory you're giving him tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.68,0:14:25.27,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Cassie.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.35,0:14:29.44,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,His heart will stop at the very sight of you or he doesn't deserve to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.06,0:14:34.44,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,And yes I'm aware of the contradiction embodied in that sentence.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.36,0:14:37.61,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.45,0:14:44.24,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Jane! - Henry!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.54,0:14:50.04,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,You look wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.83,0:14:52.92,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Well hello John. It's very good to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.00,0:14:55.84,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Nice to see you. - Oh John!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.92,0:14:59.13,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,George!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.97,0:15:03.01,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave your brother alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.27,0:15:11.15,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Jane! Jane? Have you heard? My father's nephew is staying with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.23,0:15:12.40,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,From London.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.48,0:15:14.07,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- He is a... - A brilliant young lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.15,0:15:16.23,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Lucy please. - With a reputation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.32,0:15:17.49,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,For lateness?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.74,0:15:22.82,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Hat off George. Hat off Father's ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.66,0:15:26.45,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Thank you John. - Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.54,0:15:30.08,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,The family is always moving in great ways and small.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.17,0:15:36.05,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Firstly the small. Henry is back from Oxford with his degree
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.84,0:15:38.47,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- thank goodness. - Well done.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.55,0:15:42.84,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,And our friend John my new student. Then the great.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.93,0:15:47.43,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Cassandra who is forsaking us for her brother Edward and his family at the coast
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.39,0:15:52.27,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,whilst Robert voyages to the West Indies with Lord Craven's expedition.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.35,0:15:56.16,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,And then together they can embark on that most great
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.16,0:15:59.03,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,and most serious journey of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.53,0:16:03.36,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Austen I understand you will be favouring us with a reading?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.45,0:16:05.20,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Do Jane. - Do.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.28,0:16:07.29,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Oh please Miss Jane. - Oh yes Jane do.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.37,0:16:08.75,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Please Jane.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.59,0:16:21.93,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"Advice from a young lady on the engagement of her beloved sister Cassandra
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.05,0:16:24.55,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"to a Fowle."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.35,0:16:33.85,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"His addresses were offered in a manner violent enough to be flattering.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.94,0:16:38.40,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"The boundaries of propriety were vigorously assaulted as was only right
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.53,0:16:41.61,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"but not quite breached as was also right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.69,0:16:43.78,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"Nevertheless she was... "
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.79,0:16:59.05,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,And may I introduce my young nephew Mr Thomas Lefroy?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.63,0:17:00.71,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.34,0:17:05.14,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,And he's more than welcome. Join us sir join us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.85,0:17:09.97,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Green velvet coat. Vastly fashionable.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.60,0:17:15.06,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll find this vastly amusing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.44,0:17:20.40,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"His addresses were...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.36,0:17:26.78,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"The boundaries of propriety were vigorously assaulted
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.87,0:17:31.58,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"as was only right but not quite breached as was also right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.66,0:17:33.58,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"Nevertheless she was not pleased.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.66,0:17:38.50,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"Her taste was refined her sentiments noble her person lovely her figure elegant."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.92,0:17:45.01,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Good God there's writing on both sides of those pages.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.09,0:17:46.43,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Shh. Damn it man.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.18,0:17:51.26,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"'It was only yesterday I repelled Lord Graham and his six million
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.35,0:17:54.81,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"'which would have lasted me almost a twelvemonth
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.89,0:17:56.64,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"'with economies... '
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.32,0:18:05.40,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"'greater than all the jewels in India an adoring heart."'
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.49,0:18:06.61,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,God!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.70,0:18:09.82,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"'And pray madam what am I to expect in return? '
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.33,0:18:13.91,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"'Expect? Well you may expect to have me pleased from time to time."'
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.00,0:18:15.54,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this who I am?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.83,0:18:22.05,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"And a sweet gentle pleading innocent
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.13,0:18:26.00,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"delicate sympathetic loyal"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.00,0:18:28.73,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"untutored adoring female heart."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.97,0:18:35.27,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,The end.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.60,0:18:39.31,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Bravo Jane. - Well done Jane.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.27,0:18:42.57,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Bravo.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.53,0:18:44.90,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Well done.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.57,0:18:52.37,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,She speaks so well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.29,0:18:59.12,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Well excessively charming I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.33,0:19:03.13,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Well accomplished enough perhaps
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.21,0:19:08.34,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,but a metropolitan mind may be less susceptible to extended juvenile self - regard.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.39,0:19:14.01,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Well thank you. We're both very proud.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.49,0:19:33.16,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,# In airy dreams #
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.17,0:19:45.67,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,# absent love to see #
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.77,0:20:01.56,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,# Dear you oh to think #
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.10,0:20:07.94,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,# On thee #
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.35,0:20:44.69,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Careful there old fellow.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.15,0:20:47.98,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine piece Mr Lefroy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.19,0:20:50.49,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Handled a gun before have you Tom?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.57,0:20:51.65,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Mmm. - Tom!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.11,0:20:55.32,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Jesus!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.08,0:21:05.33,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Tom. - Uncle?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.29,0:21:08.71,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not try a walk?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.59,0:21:14.26,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,There's some very fine country round about. Very fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.97,0:21:16.09,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,A walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.19,0:22:11.36,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.15,0:22:13.74,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss! Miss!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.11,0:22:15.74,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss! Miss I...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.62,0:22:20.78,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.41,0:22:24.50,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.58,0:22:27.33,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Miss... - Austen.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.08,0:22:29.67,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr Lefroy.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.67,0:22:32.88,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes I know but I am alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.88,0:22:35.84,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Except for me. - Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.92,0:22:37.63,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh come!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.72,0:22:41.51,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,What rules of conduct apply in this rural situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.60,0:22:44.35,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,We have been introduced have we not?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.39,0:22:50.10,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,What value is there in an introduction when you cannot even remember my name?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.23,0:22:53.53,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed can barely stay awake in my presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.40,0:22:56.53,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Madam.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.61,0:23:00.28,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,These scruples must seem very provincial to a gentleman with such elevated airs
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.37,0:23:04.49,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,but I do not devise these rules. I am merely obliged to obey them.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.33,0:23:09.75,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I have been told there is much to see upon a walk
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.83,0:23:14.25,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,but all I've detected so far is a general tendency to green above and brown below.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.34,0:23:18.17,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes well others have detected more. It is celebrated.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.26,0:23:21.39,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- There's even a book about Selborne Wood. - Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.80,0:23:24.47,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,A novel perhaps?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.27,0:23:28.56,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Novels?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.27,0:23:35.53,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Being poor insipid things read by mere women even God forbid written by mere women?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.61,0:23:37.19,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I see we're talking of your reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.28,0:23:41.32,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,As if the writing of women did not display the greatest powers of mind
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.41,0:23:44.78,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,knowledge of human nature the liveliest effusions of wit and humour
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.87,0:23:47.75,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,and the best - chosen language imaginable?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.83,0:23:50.92,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Was I deficient in rapture? - In consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.13,0:23:53.75,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,It was...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.05,0:24:00.30,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,It was accomplished.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.22,0:24:08.77,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,It was ironic.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.98,0:24:17.44,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- And you're sure I've not offended you? - Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.16,0:24:33.46,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,My lords ladies and gentlemen the Grand Vizier's Flight.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.55,0:24:40.76,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- May I have the honour? - How kind cousin.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.60,0:24:51.18,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Miss Austen. - Mr Wisley.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.19,0:24:55.19,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,May I have the pleasure of this next dance?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.32,0:25:04.16,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Oh no we're so late. - Take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.45,0:25:06.12,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh thank you Tom.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.20,0:25:07.41,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Hurry. - Lucy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.43,0:25:28.64,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.43,0:25:35.02,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I am mortified.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.52,0:25:39.44,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I practised but it won't stick.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.62,0:25:51.49,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,What a lovely pair they make.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.50,0:25:55.04,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah Sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.12,0:25:58.75,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- What do you make of Mr Lefroy? - We're honoured by his presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.84,0:25:59.88,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,You think?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.96,0:26:02.59,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,He does with his preening prancing Irish - cum - Bond - Street airs.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.67,0:26:03.80,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Jane.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.88,0:26:07.76,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Well I call it very high indeed refusing to dance when there are so few gentleman.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.84,0:26:10.43,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Henry are all your friends so disagreeable? - Jane.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.51,0:26:12.60,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Where exactly in Ireland does he come from anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.68,0:26:14.56,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Limerick Miss Austen.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.19,0:26:25.32,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I would regard it as a mark of extreme favour
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.40,0:26:28.95,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,if you would stoop to honour me with this next dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.54,0:26:38.58,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Being the first to dance with me madam I feel it only fair to inform you
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.67,0:26:42.09,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,that you carry the standard for Hampshire hospitality.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.17,0:26:45.47,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah then your country reputation depends on my report.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.55,0:26:50.30,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,This by the way is called a country dance after the French contredanse.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.81,0:26:57.48,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Not because it is exhibited at an uncouth rural assembly
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.56,0:26:59.31,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,with glutinous pies
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.07,0:27:03.57,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,execrable Madeira
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.32,0:27:06.95,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,and truly anarchic dancing.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.03,0:27:09.45,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,You judge the company severely madam.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.82,0:27:13.08,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- I was describing what you'd be thinking. - Allow me to think for myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.16,0:27:16.41,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Gives me leave to do the same sir and come to a different conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.50,0:27:20.21,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Will you give so much to a woman? - It must depend on the woman
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.29,0:27:22.34,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,and what she thinks of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.63,0:27:27.72,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,But you are above being pleased.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.22,0:27:32.51,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,And I think that you miss what was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.60,0:27:35.01,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Austen. Mr? - Lefroy.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.98,0:27:42.90,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I think that you Miss Austen consider yourself a cut above the company.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.57,0:27:45.69,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.90,0:27:49.57,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,You ma'am
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.53,0:27:52.78,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,secretly.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.67,0:28:06.55,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,How many times did you stand up with that gentleman Jane?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.63,0:28:08.59,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Was it twice? - Twice would have been partial.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.67,0:28:11.34,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Thrice would have been absolutely... - Flagrant.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.43,0:28:15.81,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Careful Jane Lucy is right. Mr Lefroy does have a reputation.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.89,0:28:18.39,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Presumably as the most disagreeable...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.48,0:28:22.56,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"... insolent arrogant impudent
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.44,0:28:29.19,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"insufferable impertinent of men."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.95,0:28:37.83,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Too many adjectives.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.26,0:28:53.38,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,What is she trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.97,0:28:56.60,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,On your toes gentlemen. No singles.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.64,0:29:03.73,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Bowler's end bowler's end.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.57,0:29:09.48,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Again! - Run for more.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.57,0:29:12.65,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I never feel more French than when I watch cricket.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.41,0:29:15.49,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Out. - Not out.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.57,0:29:16.66,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- No? - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.74,0:29:18.41,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Is he out?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.79,0:29:26.96,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I begin to suspect you're flirting with my brother cousin.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.04,0:29:30.96,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Flirting is a woman's trade. One must keep in practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.38,0:29:34.76,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,You're gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.22,0:29:36.89,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Well played Tom.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.06,0:29:41.22,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,We're depending on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.14,0:29:44.89,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh it's Mr Warren's... turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.48,0:29:47.86,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Best of luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.94,0:29:49.40,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,John Warren!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.94,0:29:52.74,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Good luck Mr Warren.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.24,0:29:55.53,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,John never was very good though.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.46,0:30:09.17,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Easy!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.17,0:30:12.63,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Run Warren run!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.71,0:30:14.05,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Quickly hurry! - Run!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.13,0:30:15.80,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Jolly good show!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.59,0:30:17.84,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.55,0:30:21.14,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- You're out. - Yah!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.22,0:30:22.81,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- You're gone Mr Warren. - Oh dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.89,0:30:24.77,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Prodigious Tom prodigious.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.40,0:30:30.36,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you Warren. On your way.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.44,0:30:32.07,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Same again Tom.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.40,0:30:38.24,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Well done Mr Warren. - Bad ball. It's a terrible wicket.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.32,0:30:41.58,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you're not too disappointed Miss Austen.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.87,0:30:44.83,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Four more to win Wisley.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.79,0:30:49.13,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Who's next? - Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.34,0:30:51.88,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- She can't... - Jane!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.96,0:30:54.46,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,What on earth are you going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.55,0:30:56.84,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Irrepressible. - she can.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.85,0:31:11.15,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Move in!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.15,0:31:13.65,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Go easy Tom.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.70,0:31:20.49,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Be gentle Lefroy!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.76,0:31:44.85,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Run Jane run!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.93,0:31:46.98,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Move! - Run!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.43,0:31:50.23,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Only four more to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.60,0:31:53.19,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Bowler's end! Move yourself you lout!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.61,0:31:58.57,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- One more! - Quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.11,0:32:00.53,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Go go go!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.61,0:32:01.95,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Not out.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.99,0:32:06.24,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Bad luck Lefroy.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.50,0:32:12.63,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.05,0:32:18.72,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,She was so good.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.51,0:32:27.56,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- You've played this game before? - No choice you see. She was raised by brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.64,0:32:29.73,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Time for a swim I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.90,0:32:35.32,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Well played Henry.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.40,0:32:38.65,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I dedicate our victory to La Comtesse de Feuillide.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.36,0:32:45.83,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Now there's a decent bit of river over the hill. - Oh yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.25,0:32:52.54,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Careful!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.31,0:33:11.89,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.77,0:33:14.98,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.48,0:33:21.90,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Not this time Lefroy. - Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.99,0:33:23.28,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,You think not?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.64,0:33:50.97,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Down boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.48,0:33:56.86,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Father have you seen Tom? - No Lucy I've not.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.82,0:34:06.36,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Besotted. Natural enough at 15.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.07,0:34:09.53,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Love and sense are enemies at any age.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.62,0:34:13.75,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Mrs Lefroy may I explore your library? - Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.29,0:34:19.46,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy would marry him tomorrow and what a terrible husband he would make.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.54,0:34:24.26,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose you mean his reputation. Experience can recommend a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.55,0:35:07.84,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Miss Austen. - Oh Mr Lefroy.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.80,0:35:12.51,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- And reading. - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.14,0:35:16.81,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been looking through your book of the wood. Mr White's Natural History.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.89,0:35:17.98,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.48,0:35:22.23,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Well how do you like it? - I cannot get on. It is too disturbing.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.65,0:35:24.23,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Disturbing? - Mmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.44,0:35:27.74,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Take this observation.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.03,0:35:33.66,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"Swifts on a fine morning in May flying this way that way
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.87,0:35:38.08,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"sailing around at a great height perfectly happily. Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.75,0:35:44.00,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"Then one leaps onto the back of another grasps tightly
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.09,0:35:47.50,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"and forgetting to fly they both sink down"
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.50,0:35:50.81,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"and down in a great dying fall"
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.59,0:35:55.72,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"fathom after fathom until the female utters... "
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.35,0:36:02.44,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.53,0:36:10.82,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"... the female utters a loud piercing cry
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.08,0:36:15.33,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"of ecstasy."
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.71,0:36:24.34,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this conduct commonplace in the natural history of Hampshire?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.84,0:36:35.68,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Your ignorance is understandable since you lack... What shall we call it?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.39,0:36:38.56,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,The history?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.10,0:36:44.36,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Propriety commands me to ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.44,0:36:49.28,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Condemns you to it and your writing to the status of female accomplishment.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.11,0:36:55.28,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,If you wish to practise the art of fiction to be the equal of a masculine author
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.66,0:36:58.24,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,experience is vital.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.16,0:37:02.37,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.88,0:37:08.38,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,And what qualifies you to offer this advice?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.17,0:37:10.42,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I know more of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.13,0:37:14.55,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,A great deal more I gather.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.05,0:37:20.89,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Enough to know that your horizons must be... widened
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.44,0:37:25.56,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,by an extraordinary young man.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.19,0:37:28.94,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,By a very dangerous young man
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.03,0:37:31.90,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,one who has no doubt infected the hearts of many a young...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.99,0:37:35.66,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Young woman with the soft corruption... - Read this
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.08,0:37:38.79,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,and you will understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.13,0:37:51.05,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"When the philosopher heard that the fortress of virtue had already been subdued
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.34,0:37:54.47,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"he began to give a large scope to his desires.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.68,0:37:58.56,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"His appetite was not of that squeamish kind which cannot feed on a dainty
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.64,0:38:00.39,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- "because another... " - "Another has tasted it."
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.47,0:38:04.39,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- He's not tasting this dainty. - What dear?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.31,0:38:08.11,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"... nor had her face much appearance of beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.19,0:38:11.65,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"But her clothes being torn from all the upper part of her body... "
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.73,0:38:16.32,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"... her breasts which were well formed and extremely white
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.91,0:38:21.62,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"attracted the eyes of her deliverer and for a few moments they stood silent... "
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.70,0:38:23.79,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"... and gazing at each other."
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.23,0:38:50.44,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I have read your book.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.03,0:38:55.45,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- I have read your book and disapprove. - Of course you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.99,0:39:00.08,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,But of what? The scenes? Characters? The prose?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.08,0:39:02.33,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,No all good.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.75,0:39:06.21,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- The morality? - Flawed.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.75,0:39:09.83,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Well of course it is. But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.92,0:39:14.17,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Vice leads to difficulty virtue to reward. Bad characters come to bad ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.26,0:39:19.80,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly. But in life bad characters often thrive. Take yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.05,0:39:25.23,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,And a novel must show how the world truly is
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.48,0:39:29.48,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,how characters genuinely think how events actually occur.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.56,0:39:35.19,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,A novel should somehow reveal the true source of our actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.49,0:39:39.32,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,What of my hero's feelings?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.78,0:39:44.49,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Well it seems to me sir that your hero's very vigorous feelings
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.58,0:39:47.83,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,caused him and everyone connected with him a great deal of trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.91,0:39:50.46,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah well if the book has troubled you...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.79,0:39:54.25,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Oh but an orphan must know trouble. - What sort of trouble?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.09,0:39:56.84,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,All sorts of trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.35,0:40:09.94,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Laverton Fair. Vastly entertaining. Monstrous good idea Jane.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.02,0:40:13.36,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes Miss Austen not exactly your usual society I'd say.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.44,0:40:15.82,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Show a little imagination Mr Lefroy.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.56,0:40:48.18,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Trouble here enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.27,0:40:51.23,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,And freedom the freedom of men.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.64,0:40:53.40,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Do not you envy it?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.48,0:40:57.36,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,But I have the intense pleasure of observing it so closely.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.03,0:41:02.11,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.20,0:41:05.24,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Now there's a fool to go to it with a professional.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.91,0:41:10.04,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- You know about this of course. - Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.16,0:41:13.08,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes a vastly fashionable pastime in London.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.09,0:41:24.01,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Beating a man to a pulp. What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.64,0:41:28.93,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr Lefroy stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.39,0:41:30.64,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Make way!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.19,0:41:38.40,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Stop! - Let us see how you fare against me sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.40,0:41:40.69,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Coming through.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.03,0:41:49.37,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Five shillings on the gent. Who will take it? You sir? That's the ticket.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.50,0:41:52.75,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Have that.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.58,0:41:55.67,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.00,0:41:57.84,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Go on hit him!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.26,0:42:02.72,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on Lefroy hit him man!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.38,0:42:07.30,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom you must stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.60,0:42:12.18,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on Lefroy!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.15,0:42:16.56,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Up sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.48,0:42:20.69,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.28,0:42:24.74,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.41,0:42:34.50,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- That's twice he's done that to me. - You spend money like water.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.67,0:42:38.17,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm afraid it's damn low water with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.33,0:42:40.67,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- I'm afraid I'm short sir. - Take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.26,0:42:44.01,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,How embarrassing.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.72,0:42:46.84,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeh!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.43,0:42:51.10,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr Lefroy? Mr Lefroy? Mr Lefroy?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.64,0:42:58.86,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Was I deficient in propriety?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.57,0:43:03.65,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.49,0:43:07.74,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Couldn't waste all those expensive boxing lessons.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.83,0:43:13.29,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me if I suspect in you a sense of justice.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.08,0:43:22.09,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I am a lawyer. Justice plays no part in the law.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.67,0:43:25.42,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that what you believe?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.38,0:43:29.93,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe it. I must.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.97,0:43:35.39,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I beg your leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.36,0:43:48.28,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Her heart is stirred. - It's a summer squall.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.66,0:43:50.66,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr Lefroy will soon be gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.66,0:43:55.01,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,And Mr Wisley will still be waiting I hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.50,0:43:58.75,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- The man's a booby. - Oh he will grow out of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.83,0:44:01.63,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,And she could fix him with very little trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.75,0:44:04.50,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,You could persuade her.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.59,0:44:06.21,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,To sacrifice her happiness?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.71,0:44:11.72,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Jane should have not the man who offers the best price but the man she wants.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.80,0:44:13.47,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh Mr Austen.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.06,0:44:18.02,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Must we have this conversation day in and day out?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.10,0:44:21.48,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll end up in the gutter if we carry on like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.75,0:44:42.29,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Jenny! Mr Austen!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.42,0:44:45.71,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.90,0:45:13.24,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,So kind of you to return the call.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.62,0:45:20.79,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Will you take a dish of tea ma'am? - Green tea?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.71,0:45:25.08,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Brown Your Ladyship. - Then no.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.01,0:45:33.05,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is your youngest daughter?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.64,0:45:37.10,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,She's visiting the poor ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.44,0:45:52.82,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Jane? Jane!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.24,0:46:00.35,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,At last. Lady Gresham and Mr Wisley have come to call.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.35,0:46:02.50,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Where have you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.87,0:46:05.38,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am. Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.04,0:46:11.59,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Well perhaps... Perhaps the young people would like to take a walk?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.67,0:46:15.55,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I see there's a pretty little wilderness at the side of the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.18,0:46:18.56,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.06,0:46:24.48,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Jane?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.94,0:46:30.32,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- What is she doing? - Writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.32,0:46:34.32,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Can anything be done about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.78,0:46:43.12,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Austen you may know
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.20,0:46:46.12,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,that I have known you
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.21,0:46:50.17,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,for some considerable time during my visits to Steventon.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.25,0:46:55.01,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,The garden is so affecting in this season.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.93,0:46:57.18,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.68,0:47:02.85,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- The impression you have given me has always... - The flowers particularly.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.60,0:47:06.81,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,What I'm trying to say is that I...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.90,0:47:09.23,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a respectable property of 2000 a year
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.31,0:47:12.15,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,in addition to even greater expectations as Lady Gresham's heir
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.23,0:47:16.03,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- to which it may be indelicate to refer. - Oh indelicate yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.11,0:47:20.12,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,It's yours. If we marry all of it yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.87,0:47:25.46,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr Wisley...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.29,0:47:33.69,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Your offer is most sincere I can see and
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.69,0:47:36.64,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,gentlemanlike and it honours me truly.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.51,0:47:43.26,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,But for all you are and all you offer I...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.48,0:47:46.56,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.74,0:48:01.32,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes affection is a shy flower that takes time to blossom.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.41,0:48:13.25,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Lying to tradesmen mending scratching scraping.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.34,0:48:16.76,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Endlessly endlessly making do!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.84,0:48:19.38,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand that our circumstances are difficult ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.47,0:48:23.64,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- There is no money for you. - Surely something could be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.72,0:48:28.52,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,What we can put by must go to your brothers. You will have nothing unless you marry.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.60,0:48:32.23,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then I will have nothing. For I will not marry without affection like my mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.31,0:48:35.57,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,And now I have to dig my own damn potatoes!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.83,0:48:50.67,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you rather be a poor old maid? Ridiculous despised the butt of jokes?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.12,0:48:55.67,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,The legitimate sport of any village lout with a stone and an impudent tongue?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.93,0:49:05.64,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Affection is desirable.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.89,0:49:10.81,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Money is absolutely indispensable.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.69,0:49:20.32,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I could live by my...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.28,0:49:25.41,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Your what?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.33,0:49:29.41,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- I could live by my... - Pen?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.46,0:49:33.12,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's knock that notion on the head once and for all.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.21,0:49:34.54,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.17,0:49:38.34,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Trouble amongst my women?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.17,0:49:40.34,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Come
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.51,0:49:43.55,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,take hands and there's an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.64,0:49:47.18,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Where are you going? Miss! - To feed the pigs ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.99,0:50:07.16,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,He could give you a splendid home.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.91,0:50:11.16,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- A comfortable life. - Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.83,0:50:13.92,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Consider.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.21,0:50:17.92,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,This is likely to be your best offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.55,0:50:19.80,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Wisley?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.38,0:50:23.34,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,It is true so far he has not impressed...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.42,0:50:26.80,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- A booby. - He should grow out of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.19,0:50:43.03,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing destroys spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.74,0:50:46.24,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,like poverty.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.25,0:51:01.09,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw Queen Marie Antoinette wear something the same at a ball once.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.01,0:51:06.76,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I making a show? I am I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.10,0:51:13.56,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,What trouble we take to make them like us when we like them.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.52,0:51:17.60,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Henry?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.77,0:51:25.45,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Eliza my brother is much younger than you. - And poorer.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.24,0:51:31.08,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,He knows that I care for him sincerely.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.87,0:51:33.54,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I know that he is handsome...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.62,0:51:36.62,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,And the handsome young men must have something to live on as well as the plain.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.71,0:51:38.96,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,You encourage him to take you for money?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.04,0:51:41.42,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Men do. - That does not make it honourable.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.50,0:51:43.34,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Well I'm a sensible woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.34,0:51:46.93,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I thank God I am not by your description.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.01,0:51:52.60,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,If you were you might have ascertained that your Irish friend has no money not a penny
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.68,0:51:55.43,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,and could not be expected to marry without it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.23,0:51:58.39,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Consider that at the ball tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.94,0:52:04.73,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,In any event he'll be gone tomorrow back to Bond Street where he can do no more harm.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.01,0:53:59.85,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Good evening Miss Austen.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.23,0:54:03.31,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.42,0:57:18.88,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Jane Austen.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.47,0:57:20.59,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.51,0:57:24.72,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,We're very honoured to be here at your aunt's ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.93,0:57:27.18,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,You dance with passion.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.31,0:57:33.40,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,No sensible woman would demonstrate passion if the purpose were to attract a husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.98,0:57:39.19,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- As opposed to a lover? - Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.16,0:57:46.41,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Rest easy Mr Lefroy.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.49,0:57:48.95,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- I have no expectation on either account. - I did not mean to offend or hurt...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.04,0:57:53.58,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no no of course not. Excuse me I'm just over warm.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.33,0:57:55.46,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon me.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.10,0:58:09.47,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Ah Miss Austen. - Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.51,0:58:49.31,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,This is unbearable. My father is pressing for an early ordination
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.39,0:58:54.94,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,while my own inclination is to the scarlet of a captaincy in His Majesty's regulars.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.02,0:58:58.73,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,But I do not have the money to purchase one.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.07,0:59:01.40,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.28,0:59:08.87,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Well that of course is impossible. - Oh Henry do not disguise yourself not to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.12,0:59:16.92,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,The scarlet will suit you very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.84,0:59:22.51,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Austen? There you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.89,0:59:37.44,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Austen I cannot believe I am obliged to have this conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.86,0:59:39.98,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Your Ladyship?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.52,0:59:45.70,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr Wisley's mother my own dear sister died young.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.91,0:59:48.87,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no children of my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.95,0:59:53.62,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you never come to understand the pain of that condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.41,1:00:00.88,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Let us simply say my nephew's wishes are close to my heart
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.63,1:00:05.01,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,however extraordinary they may be.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.38,1:00:09.47,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Well
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.76,1:00:12.93,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,your health seems robust.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.10,1:00:16.68,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,You have the usual accomplishments.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.85,1:00:20.40,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Your person is agreeable.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.02,1:00:28.32,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,But when a young woman such as yourself receives the addresses
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.40,1:00:33.95,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,from a gentleman such as my nephew it is her duty to accept at once.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.04,1:00:36.66,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,But what do we find?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.62,1:00:40.63,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Independent thought? - Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.96,1:00:47.47,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,My nephew Miss Austen condescends far indeed
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.76,1:00:52.51,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,in offering to the daughter of an obscure and impecunious clergyman.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.60,1:00:56.27,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Impecunious? Your Ladyship is mistaken.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.98,1:00:59.23,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I am never mistaken.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.23,1:01:04.15,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Your father is in grave financial difficulties.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.28,1:01:07.24,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,But all is not lost.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.70,1:01:12.49,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,He has a daughter upon whom fortune has smiled.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.13,1:01:31.68,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr Wisley is a good opportunity for Jane.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.01,1:01:35.35,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,She should accept him at once.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.43,1:01:40.10,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Do not you think?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.98,1:01:44.06,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Lucy let us take some refreshments. - What? Mother.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.67,1:02:13.89,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I have learned of Mr Wisley's marriage proposal.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.51,1:02:17.01,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,My congratulations.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.60,1:02:23.10,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there an alternative for a well - educated young woman of small fortune?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.40,1:02:26.19,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,How can you have him?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.44,1:02:29.48,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Even with his thousands and his houses
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.57,1:02:33.82,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,how can you of all people dispose of yourself without affection?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.62,1:02:40.33,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,How can I dispose of myself with it?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.25,1:02:45.38,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,You are leaving tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.75,1:03:25.92,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Did I do that well? - Very very well.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.88,1:03:31.38,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted just once to do it well.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.68,1:03:40.85,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no money no property
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.93,1:03:44.64,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I am entirely dependent upon that bizarre old lunatic my uncle.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.73,1:03:49.31,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot yet offer marriage. But you must know what I feel.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.48,1:03:52.19,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Jane I'm yours.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.07,1:03:57.78,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Gah I'm yours. I'm yours heart and soul.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.99,1:04:02.04,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Much good that is.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.04,1:04:05.08,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me decide that.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.79,1:04:12.30,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,What will we do?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.38,1:04:16.67,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,What we must.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.72,1:04:28.60,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"My dearest Cassandra my heart has wings.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.69,1:04:31.40,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"Doubts and deliberations are ended.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.48,1:04:36.61,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"Soon I shall escape the attentions of that great lady and her scintillating nephew.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.28,1:04:40.37,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"Eliza Henry and I will join you at the coast
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.45,1:04:43.24,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"but we are obliged to break our journey in London.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.33,1:04:47.04,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"Tom has cleverly secured an invitation to stay with his uncle the judge.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.12,1:04:50.00,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"Let us hope we can convince him of my eligibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.08,1:04:51.96,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"Please destroy this disgraceful letter
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.04,1:04:54.50,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"the moment you have recovered from your astonishment.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.59,1:04:58.17,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"Yours affectionately and in haste Jane."
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.43,1:05:06.10,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom! Our guests have arrived.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.15,1:05:15.23,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Decorum.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.94,1:05:17.07,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Countess.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.90,1:05:19.07,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.15,1:05:20.78,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Welcome... - Madame le Comtesse.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.86,1:05:22.51,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Madame le Comtesse.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.51,1:05:27.40,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Seldom too seldom my house receives the presence of nobility.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.87,1:05:30.17,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,And of course its friends. Please.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.42,1:05:34.50,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Your stay is short. There's not a moment to lose.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.75,1:05:40.59,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,My nephew has devised a plan of metropolitan amusement.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.09,1:05:45.35,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Pleasure is as you would say Madame his forte.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.43,1:05:46.72,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah is it?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.48,1:05:51.69,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Which battle was it Tom?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.77,1:05:52.98,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Villers - en - Cauchies.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.06,1:05:57.86,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Very good. Thousands slain. Served those Frenchies out.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.94,1:06:02.28,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. Saving your presence ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.36,1:06:05.45,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Be not afraid of abusing the Jacobins on my account Judge.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.53,1:06:09.45,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- They guillotined my husband. - Oh savages. Beasts.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.54,1:06:11.75,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- And his property? - Confiscated.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.50,1:06:13.58,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,A disaster.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.08,1:06:17.42,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course by then much of my wealth was portable so...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.42,1:06:21.88,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes portable property is happiness in a pocketbook.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.72,1:06:28.22,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Do I detect you in irony?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.52,1:06:37.82,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,It is my considered opinion that irony is insult with a smiling face.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.23,1:06:40.28,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.40,1:06:42.49,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.61,1:06:45.70,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,No?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.20,1:06:51.50,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,No irony is the bringing together of contradictory truths
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.96,1:06:55.71,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,to make out of the contradiction a new truth with a laugh or a smile
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.79,1:06:59.71,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,and I confess that a truth must come with one or the other
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.80,1:07:04.55,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,or I account it as false and a denial of the very nature of humanity itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.18,1:07:15.69,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,My cousin is a writer.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.23,1:07:19.61,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Of what? - Jane?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.15,1:07:24.24,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Novels.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.28,1:07:28.83,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,A young woman of family?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.54,1:07:34.96,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes uncle and tomorrow we go and visit another Mrs Radcliffe.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.00,1:07:39.54,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,She keeps herself to herself almost a recluse but I know her husband through the law.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.63,1:07:43.09,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Who? - The authoress Mrs Radcliffe.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.47,1:07:46.18,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- As writing is her profession. - Her what?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.26,1:07:48.97,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,500 uncle for the last novel The Mysteries of Udolpho.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.05,1:07:51.72,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- And 800 I believe for her next. - The Italian.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.81,1:07:53.93,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Above 1000?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.56,1:07:59.94,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,The times the times.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.79,1:08:16.41,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,You live so quietly.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:16.50,1:08:21.04,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,And yet your novels are filled with romance danger terror.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.21,1:08:25.13,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything my life is not.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.51,1:08:28.68,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.47,1:08:31.43,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Of what do you wish to write?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.10,1:08:35.52,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Of the heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.68,1:08:38.35,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know it?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.52,1:08:40.98,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Not all of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.15,1:08:43.94,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,In time you will.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.82,1:08:49.24,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,But even if that fails that's what the imagination is for.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.45,1:08:56.75,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Your imagination has brought you independence.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.58,1:09:02.46,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,At a cost to myself and to my husband.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.88,1:09:05.13,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Poor William.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.13,1:09:08.93,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,To have a wife who has a mind is considered not quite proper.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.01,1:09:13.14,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,To have a wife with a literary reputation nothing short of scandalous.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.52,1:09:20.56,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,But it must be possible?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.60,1:09:24.32,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- To live as both wife and author? - Oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.32,1:09:26.53,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I think so.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.57,1:09:29.99,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Though never easy.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.57,1:10:10.32,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Could I really have this?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.11,1:10:12.66,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,What precisely?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.66,1:10:14.99,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,You.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.99,1:10:17.24,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Me how?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.20,1:10:21.16,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- This life with you. - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.37,1:10:24.63,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Lefroy.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.71,1:10:26.96,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Hush. The judge. - The man's like a rampant dog.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.76,1:10:33.43,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,He will be generous. I'm sure of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.68,1:10:37.14,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- You'll speak with him? - Tomorrow I promise.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.22,1:10:39.52,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I really must say good night.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.27,1:10:42.44,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Good night. - Good night.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.81,1:10:47.61,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Miss Austen? - Yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.23,1:10:49.65,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Good night.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.87,1:11:00.66,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,You know I think my mother is right. A husband and the sooner the better.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.79,1:11:50.04,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Five girls of little fortune.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.69,1:12:04.98,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"... sensibly and as warmly as a man violently in love can be supposed to do."
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.52,1:12:11.52,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"Mr Wickham was the happy man towards whom almost every female eye was turned.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.53,1:12:20.78,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"... partial prejudiced absurd.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.79,1:12:24.95,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"Watch for the first appearance of Pemberley Woods.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.62,1:12:29.63,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"The happiness which this reply produced...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.71,1:12:33.51,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"It will not do. My feelings will not be repressed."
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.60,1:13:28.02,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Good morning sir. - Good morning?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.44,1:13:35.61,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Has the world turned topsy? - Sir?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:37.40,1:13:40.41,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I trust the countess is enjoying her visit?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.74,1:13:45.20,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- I gather she is sir. I... - Fine woman very fine woman.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.70,1:13:47.91,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.33,1:13:53.33,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- I'd hoped to discuss a certain matter. - Your allowance is beyond negotiation.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.17,1:14:04.14,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you have had the opportunity to become acquainted with Miss Austen yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.22,1:14:08.81,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I am sure you will find as I do that she is a remarkable young woman.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:11.98,1:14:14.61,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- This is an outrage! - Lf you will allow me to speak sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.69,1:14:18.40,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no need. This letter makes it absolutely clear.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.49,1:14:19.57,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Letter?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:19.65,1:14:22.91,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I know what you were at down in Hampshire.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:23.45,1:14:25.20,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- It is from Steventon. - Is it true
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.28,1:14:27.66,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,that you have practiced upon me with this chit?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.74,1:14:29.58,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I wished you to know the young lady.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.66,1:14:31.71,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I wished to introduce her to your affections discreetly.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.79,1:14:35.42,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Aye! Blind me with the rich widow and then
Dialogue: 0,1:14:35.42,1:14:38.66,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,insinuate that penniless little husband-hunter!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.67,1:14:42.51,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Moderation sir I beg you! - That ironical little authoress.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.59,1:14:45.14,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I wished you to know her for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:45.72,1:14:48.56,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I was certain her merit would speak for her.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.81,1:14:52.69,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Consider sir my happiness is in your hands. - Happiness?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:55.65,1:14:56.69,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it nephew
Dialogue: 0,1:14:56.77,1:15:00.61,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I had rather you were a whore - mongering blackguard with a chance of reform
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.69,1:15:04.49,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,than a love - sick whelp sunk in a bad marriage.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.26,1:15:23.09,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,My uncle has refused to give his consent.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.26,1:15:27.43,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- The letter has done its work. - Who sent it?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.52,1:15:32.02,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Lady Gresham?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.64,1:15:35.02,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Or her nephew.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.70,1:15:47.78,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,They think that they can do what they like with us but I will not accept this.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.87,1:15:49.66,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,We have no choice.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.74,1:15:52.33,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course we do.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.12,1:15:57.25,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.38,1:16:07.59,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I depend entirely upon...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.77,1:16:15.81,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Upon your uncle.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.64,1:16:18.02,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Mmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.77,1:16:21.61,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,And I depend on you.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.24,1:16:30.12,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,So what will you do?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.16,1:16:34.62,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,What I must.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.54,1:16:40.00,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a duty to my family Jane. I must think of them as well as...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.08,1:16:41.17,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.05,1:16:48.09,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that... Is that all you have to say to me?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.78,1:17:06.44,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye Mr Lefroy.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:01.46,1:18:05.34,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,The sentence of this court is that you be taken to the place whence you came
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.42,1:18:08.84,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,and thence to a place of execution
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.34,1:18:14.10,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,and that you be there hanged by the neck until you are dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.05,1:18:17.85,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,May the Lord have mercy on your soul.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.19,1:18:28.40,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Next.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.12,1:18:43.88,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,He has behaved so ill to you Jane.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.38,1:18:52.47,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps soon we can return home to Steventon.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.76,1:18:56.85,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there any news of Robert?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.52,1:19:05.81,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,He has arrived in San Domingo at last.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.90,1:19:07.07,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.19,1:19:10.28,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.18,1:19:37.60,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Glass of wine with you sir?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.26,1:19:40.35,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:40.93,1:19:44.23,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes a toast from one member of the profession to another.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:59.84,1:21:03.31,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry to have been so disobliging in the past.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:09.19,1:21:10.69,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr Wisley?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.44,1:21:20.03,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,So the infamous Mrs Radcliffe.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.53,1:21:23.33,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Was she really as gothic as her novels?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.29,1:21:28.50,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Not in externals
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.58,1:21:31.54,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,but her inner landscape is quite picturesque I suspect.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.63,1:21:33.17,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,True of us all.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:32.23,1:22:34.81,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a message for Reverend Austen.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.24,1:22:42.91,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Message for Reverend Austen. - Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.60,1:23:09.93,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Uncle?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:26.28,1:23:27.70,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.97,1:24:32.64,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,It seemed he died very soon after landing in San Domingo.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:32.93,1:24:35.19,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,My God he was hardly there.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:36.14,1:24:38.06,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,What was the disease?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.36,1:24:43.15,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Yellow fever. Lord Craven he wrote.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.57,1:24:46.86,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,He said that if he had known he was engaged to be married
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.95,1:24:49.24,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,he would never have taken him.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.33,1:24:59.08,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Jane there's something else.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.84,1:25:03.17,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr Lefroy Tom.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.30,1:25:06.38,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.18,1:25:10.18,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I would keep this from you if I could.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.35,1:25:13.31,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,He's here visiting Mrs Lefroy and I...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.43,1:25:15.10,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,He is engaged.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.61,1:25:26.82,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,So soon?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.44,1:26:01.69,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,A letter?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.02,1:26:05.19,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.73,1:26:08.36,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,It's something I began in London.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.74,1:26:15.79,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,It is the tale of a young woman.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:16.49,1:26:18.16,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Two young women.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.50,1:26:22.54,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Better than their circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.96,1:26:24.46,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,So many are.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:24.54,1:26:28.55,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,And two young gentlemen who receive
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.05,1:26:31.30,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,much better than their deserts as so very many do.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.43,1:26:34.68,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Mmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.06,1:26:40.85,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,How does the story begin?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:41.44,1:26:42.94,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Badly. - And then?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:43.02,1:26:44.69,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,It gets worse.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:46.44,1:26:48.36,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,With I hope some humour.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.24,1:26:55.87,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,How does it end?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.92,1:27:04.42,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,They both make triumphant happy endings.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.67,1:27:08.34,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Brilliant marriages?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.46,1:27:11.80,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Incandescent marriages
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.43,1:27:15.14,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,to very rich men.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.15,1:27:31.65,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,You asked me a question.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.65,1:27:37.33,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I am ready to give you an answer. But there is one matter to be settled.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.08,1:27:43.33,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot make you out Mr Wisley.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.38,1:27:47.09,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,At times you are
Dialogue: 0,1:27:48.04,1:27:51.17,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,the most gentlemanlike man I know and yet you would...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:51.26,1:27:54.01,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"Yet". What a sad word.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.09,1:27:59.93,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,And yet you write yourself most tellingly to great effect.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:01.39,1:28:04.73,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- I'm speaking of course of your letter. - What letter?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.81,1:28:08.06,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Was your aunt the correspondent on your behalf?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:10.11,1:28:11.57,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,What matter?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.57,1:28:15.03,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,One way or another passion makes fools of us all.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.11,1:28:17.53,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope in time passion may regain your better opinion.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:17.62,1:28:19.58,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,The emotion is absurd.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.54,1:28:23.41,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,When you consider the sex to whom it is often directed
Dialogue: 0,1:28:23.50,1:28:25.87,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,indistinguishable from folly.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.88,1:28:32.01,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I thank you for the honour of your proposal. I accept. Good day.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.03,1:29:00.58,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,George George.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:01.24,1:29:04.79,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr Wisley is... He's an honourable man.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.87,1:29:07.04,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll always have a place with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:12.67,1:29:14.05,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Austen.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:16.30,1:29:17.84,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr Lefroy.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.85,1:29:28.02,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.32,1:29:35.78,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe I must congratulate you Mr Lefroy.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:37.49,1:29:41.49,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,And you've come to visit an old friend at such a time. How considerate.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.00,1:29:51.17,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I have come
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.25,1:29:54.17,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,to offer an explanation belatedly
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.30,1:29:59.26,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,for my conduct. I cannot think how to describe it.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.34,1:30:01.93,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me about your lady Mr Lefroy.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:03.22,1:30:05.31,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,From where does she come?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.35,1:30:09.52,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,She's from County Wexford.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.89,1:30:12.90,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Your own country. Excellent.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.32,1:30:20.74,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,What was it that won her? Your manner smiles and pleasing address?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:26.66,1:30:29.62,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,No no not at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.79,1:30:35.04,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,No had I really experienced that emotion I should at present detest
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.04,1:30:36.41,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,the very sight of him.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.42,1:30:38.30,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,And you are mistaken.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.38,1:30:42.89,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm even impartial towards the gloriously endowed Miss Wexford...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:42.97,1:30:44.64,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot do this.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.61,1:30:56.82,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,And so you would marry Wisley?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.32,1:31:04.07,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Please?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.24,1:31:11.29,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,If there is a shred of truth or justice inside of you
Dialogue: 0,1:31:11.37,1:31:13.58,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- you cannot marry him. - Oh no Mr Lefroy.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.67,1:31:16.63,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Justice by your own admission you know little of truth even less.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.71,1:31:21.30,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Jane I have tried. I have tried and I cannot live this lie.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.30,1:31:23.59,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:24.72,1:31:27.10,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Jane can you?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.18,1:31:34.81,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,What value will there be in life if we are not together?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:42.28,1:31:44.16,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Run away with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.70,1:31:48.41,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,An elopement?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:49.37,1:31:51.70,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,That is exactly what I propose.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.79,1:31:57.42,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll post to London by Friday be in Scotland and man and wife.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.92,1:32:02.38,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Leave everything? - Everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.26,1:32:05.76,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,It is the only way we can be together.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.78,1:32:27.82,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll lose everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:28.49,1:32:32.95,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Family place. For what?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.37,1:32:36.12,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,A lifetime of drudgery on a pittance?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:36.83,1:32:40.21,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,A child every year and no means to lighten the load?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:40.50,1:32:43.55,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- How will you write Jane? - I do not know.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.97,1:32:46.89,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,But happiness is within my grasp and I cannot help myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:46.97,1:32:49.10,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no sense in this.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.43,1:32:57.94,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,If you could have your Robert back even like this
Dialogue: 0,1:32:59.02,1:33:00.69,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,would you do it?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.78,1:33:11.79,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Please conceal my departure as long as possible. - Wait.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.50,1:33:15.71,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.75,1:33:20.04,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Take these. Now go quickly.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.91,1:33:59.71,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Come. If we hurry we can still make the morning coach.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:00.04,1:34:01.38,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,You are sure?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:08.09,1:34:09.43,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.59,1:34:14.35,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Is it coming? - Not yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:17.06,1:34:20.31,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Take my hand. All right?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:20.73,1:34:23.19,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry. I can hear it approaching.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:28.40,1:34:29.74,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Here it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.74,1:34:38.74,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.58,1:34:41.75,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Two to London. We'll settle at first rest.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:41.83,1:34:43.67,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Yes? - Right you are sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.41,1:35:17.66,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Hampshire your home county.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:19.29,1:35:20.62,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,It was.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.17,1:35:34.01,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Stuck. Everybody out ladies and gentlemen please.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:35.80,1:35:38.31,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- We need to lighten the load. - No let me let me.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.39,1:35:43.39,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I shall require you gentlemen to give me a hand put your shoulders into it.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.77,1:35:51.03,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Now sir if you can push on the coach itself. Excuse me sir. Young gentleman?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:51.19,1:35:54.07,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Yes yes. - You on the other side sir thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:54.57,1:35:56.95,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Young gentleman please come along. - All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.03,1:35:59.45,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Mind helping us? Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:59.87,1:36:02.54,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Right all together now then sirs please?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:07.71,1:36:09.30,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,One two
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.05,1:36:11.80,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,and a three and push!
Dialogue: 0,1:36:12.92,1:36:14.22,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:15.59,1:36:17.22,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"Dear Tom.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:17.64,1:36:20.60,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"How timely was the arrival of the money you sent."
Dialogue: 0,1:36:22.43,1:36:25.06,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,One two and three!
Dialogue: 0,1:36:30.19,1:36:33.61,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"It was so very much appreciated by your father and I.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:34.24,1:36:37.49,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"You're so kind to share your uncle's allowance.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.57,1:36:40.12,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"Indeed I do not dare think how we would survive without it."
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.17,1:36:49.25,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Well done. Thank you sirs.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:49.79,1:36:54.26,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,All right ladies and gentlemen back on the coach as soon as you can thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:04.06,1:37:05.60,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,We are ready.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:11.98,1:37:14.24,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Worried? - No.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:15.78,1:37:19.74,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Is it the loss of your reputation? - No.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:21.83,1:37:23.29,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,The loss of yours.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:23.37,1:37:27.29,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- I do not... - Please sir come along the coach is departing.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:27.37,1:37:28.58,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Come.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:04.79,1:38:07.37,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Changing horses. Twenty minutes only.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:07.46,1:38:11.79,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,House of office at the back of the inn. All down quick as you like.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:34.23,1:38:37.90,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,How many brothers and sisters do you have in Limerick Tom?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:37.99,1:38:40.36,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Enough. Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:43.74,1:38:46.49,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,What are the names of your brothers and sisters?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:46.58,1:38:48.00,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,They...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:51.58,1:38:53.75,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,On whom do they depend?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:59.09,1:39:01.13,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Your reputation is destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:03.85,1:39:07.31,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Your profligacy is a beautiful sham.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:19.11,1:39:22.49,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- I can earn money. - It will not be enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:24.53,1:39:26.08,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I will rise.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:26.91,1:39:30.66,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,With a High Court Judge as your enemy? And a penniless wife?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:31.87,1:39:34.88,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,God knows how many mouths depending on you?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:36.25,1:39:40.92,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,My sweet sweet friend you will sink and we will all sink with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.13,1:39:43.30,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- I will... - Hampshire Flyer.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:43.38,1:39:46.22,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Hampshire Flyer's leaving in five minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:50.64,1:39:54.10,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,No! No Jane.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:55.15,1:39:56.73,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I will never give you up.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:56.82,1:40:00.86,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Tom... - Don't speak or think.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:02.20,1:40:05.41,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Just love me. Do you love me?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:07.70,1:40:08.91,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:10.75,1:40:14.58,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,But if our love destroys your family it will destroy itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:14.87,1:40:16.29,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- No. - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:17.17,1:40:21.42,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,In a long slow degradation of guilt and regret and blame.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:21.51,1:40:23.05,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,That is nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:26.30,1:40:27.55,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:28.76,1:40:30.52,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Made from contradiction.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:34.10,1:40:36.48,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,But it must come with a smile.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:37.56,1:40:42.19,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Or else I shall count it as false and we shall have had no love at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:47.07,1:40:49.28,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:56.33,1:40:57.63,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:14.64,1:41:17.77,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Typical bloody runaway. "Will I won't I? "
Dialogue: 0,1:41:37.83,1:41:40.21,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss. Miss.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:45.05,1:41:46.72,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,All right off you go.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:07.55,1:43:08.92,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:13.22,1:43:17.18,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Where is everyone? - Looking for you Miss. Looking everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:18.22,1:43:20.31,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Thank you Jenny. - Mr Warren.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:24.52,1:43:28.19,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Your family tried to keep the matter from the servants but...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:29.86,1:43:33.53,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is that blackguard Lefroy? My God if Henry finds him he'll kill him.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:33.62,1:43:35.28,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,He won't find him.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:36.28,1:43:38.50,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,If he does he won't kill him.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:39.95,1:43:41.62,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no need.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:43.75,1:43:47.05,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:49.30,1:43:50.97,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:53.09,1:43:56.26,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. I see.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:06.48,1:44:07.73,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Jane
Dialogue: 0,1:44:10.65,1:44:14.03,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I may have less personal charm than Lefroy.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:15.20,1:44:17.37,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Superficial charm to some eyes.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:17.37,1:44:21.57,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,To others it is mere affectation but I...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:21.58,1:44:24.00,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- I have no hopes. - Hopes?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:26.04,1:44:28.88,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,You cannot begin to imagine.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:29.25,1:44:32.51,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for the great honour of your offer
Dialogue: 0,1:44:33.80,1:44:36.43,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,but are there no other women in Hampshire?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:57.32,1:44:59.70,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,It was you who wrote the judge.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:04.46,1:45:07.92,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,You must consider how much I have always loved you.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:56.38,1:45:57.76,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:02.64,1:46:04.56,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,You came back to us.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:32.79,1:46:34.09,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave it.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:37.92,1:46:42.01,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr Austen I must inform you that I shall not attend service today.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:42.10,1:46:44.89,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Not in the presence of this young woman. - Indeed...
Dialogue: 0,1:46:44.97,1:46:47.10,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- If I must speak plainly... - Aunt.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:47.18,1:46:51.31,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe your youngest daughter has been on a journey.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:51.40,1:46:56.11,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Her Ladyship considers travel a crime? - Unsanctioned travel.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:56.19,1:47:00.32,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore be aware that my nephew has withdrawn his addresses
Dialogue: 0,1:47:00.41,1:47:04.37,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,to someone without family fortune importance
Dialogue: 0,1:47:05.24,1:47:08.66,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,and fatally tainted by suspicion.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:08.75,1:47:13.92,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Oh she has family madam. - Indeed she has.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:15.21,1:47:19.59,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Importance may depend upon other matters than Your Ladyship can conceive.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:20.72,1:47:24.39,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,As to fortune a young woman might depend upon herself.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:26.81,1:47:29.31,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,An interesting notion Miss Austen.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:36.52,1:47:40.57,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Oblige me a walk along the river to enlarge upon the topic.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:42.86,1:47:44.16,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Wisley?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:51.92,1:47:56.88,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I am sorry if my conduct has disappointed you Mr Wisley.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:58.09,1:48:02.09,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems you cannot bring yourself to marry without affection.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:02.18,1:48:03.89,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Or even with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:05.43,1:48:09.56,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I respect you for that and share your opinion. Neither can I.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:12.27,1:48:15.36,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd always hoped to win your love in time
Dialogue: 0,1:48:15.44,1:48:19.23,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,but I am vain enough to want to be loved for myself rather than my money.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:19.32,1:48:21.32,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Do we part as friends?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:23.32,1:48:24.74,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,We do.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:27.99,1:48:30.62,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- So you will live... - By my pen. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:35.08,1:48:38.17,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Will all your stories have happy endings?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:38.88,1:48:40.80,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,My characters will have
Dialogue: 0,1:48:41.42,1:48:43.72,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,after a little bit of trouble
Dialogue: 0,1:48:45.14,1:48:47.30,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,all that they desire.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:49.68,1:48:52.60,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,The good do not always come to good ends.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:55.10,1:48:57.90,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,It is a truth universally acknowledged.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:59.23,1:49:02.15,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"... that a single man in possession of a good fortune
Dialogue: 0,1:49:02.24,1:49:04.03,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"must be in want of a wife."
Dialogue: 0,1:49:07.28,1:49:10.37,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"However little known the feelings or views of such a man may be
Dialogue: 0,1:49:10.45,1:49:12.83,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"on his first entering a neighbourhood
Dialogue: 0,1:49:12.91,1:49:16.88,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"this truth is so well fixed in the minds of the surrounding families
Dialogue: 0,1:49:18.71,1:49:23.17,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"that he is considered as the rightful property of some one or other of their daughters.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:23.26,1:49:26.47,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"'My dear Mr Bennet ' said his lady to him one day
Dialogue: 0,1:49:26.55,1:49:29.60,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"'Have you heard that Netherfield Park is let at last? '
Dialogue: 0,1:49:29.68,1:49:32.06,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"Mr Bennet replied that he had not.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:32.14,1:49:34.64,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"'But it is ' returned she... "
Dialogue: 0,1:51:27.21,1:51:30.18,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it Miss Austen? The Miss Austen?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:30.26,1:51:33.72,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,No Madam. That courtesy according to the customs of precedence
Dialogue: 0,1:51:33.80,1:51:35.81,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,belongs to my elder sister.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:35.89,1:51:39.64,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Jane Austen the authoress of Pride and Prejudice?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:39.73,1:51:43.90,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,My sister wishes to remain anonymous but your kind regard is much appreciated.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:43.98,1:51:45.86,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- Thank you. - Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:19.72,1:52:21.60,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Please come through.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:22.77,1:52:24.23,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I shall never forgive Henry for this.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:24.31,1:52:27.44,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes you will. We always forgive him for everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:32.24,1:52:34.66,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Jane an old friend.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:35.57,1:52:37.24,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Late as ever.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:39.08,1:52:41.54,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Madame le Comtesse Miss Austen.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:44.00,1:52:45.46,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr Lefroy.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:53.22,1:52:55.18,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Please allow me to introduce to you
Dialogue: 0,1:52:55.26,1:53:00.10,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,your most avid of admirers my daughter Miss Lefroy.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:01.81,1:53:04.94,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Austen what a pleasure to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:07.36,1:53:09.77,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you read for us this evening?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:09.86,1:53:12.44,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah well you see my sister never reads.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:12.53,1:53:15.61,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Otherwise how else is she supposed to remain anonymous?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:15.70,1:53:17.24,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,- But... - Jane.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:25.21,1:53:27.25,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,I will make an exception
Dialogue: 0,1:53:28.08,1:53:30.25,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,if my new friend wishes it.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:32.55,1:53:34.30,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,Come sit by me.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:45.94,1:53:47.77,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,She is lovely Tom.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:49.81,1:53:51.69,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"She began now to comprehend
Dialogue: 0,1:53:52.94,1:53:56.57,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"that he was exactly the man who in disposition and talents
Dialogue: 0,1:53:57.11,1:53:58.87,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"would most suit her.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:59.78,1:54:03.24,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"His understanding and temper though unlike her own
Dialogue: 0,1:54:03.62,1:54:06.25,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"would have answered all her wishes.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:08.33,1:54:12.09,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"It was an union that must have been to the advantage of both.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:12.17,1:54:14.30,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"By her ease and liveliness
Dialogue: 0,1:54:14.38,1:54:18.05,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"his mind might have been softened his manners improved
Dialogue: 0,1:54:18.59,1:54:23.64,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"and from his judgment information and knowledge of the world
Dialogue: 0,1:54:24.85,1:54:28.44,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"she must have received benefit of greater importance.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:29.77,1:54:34.94,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"But no such happy marriage could now teach the admiring multitude
Dialogue: 0,1:54:35.65,1:54:39.20,EnText,,0000,0000,0000,,"what connubial felicity really was."
